## .distignore — files excluded from the distributed plugin ZIP.
## Mirrors the `-x` exclude list in .github/workflows/update-release-latest.yml
## (the zip step is the actual gate; this file documents the contract and
## is what `wp dist-archive` / `svn` tooling would use).
##
## Keep `update-checker.php` in the ZIP -- the plugin self-updates from
## GitHub releases (Patcherly is NOT distributed via WordPress.org), so the
## updater is required runtime. plugin-check's `plugin_updater_detected`
## flag against that file is an accepted/expected report entry given the
## distribution channel.

# Development tests (have CLI-only guards and phpcs:disable; not for end users).
tests/

# Developer-facing README (the user-facing copy is readme.txt).
README.md

# Editor / metadata noise.
.distignore
.editorconfig
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

# OS noise.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Build / dev folders.
node_modules/
vendor/
